Aperture settings are identified with the letter f in front of them, such as f/2, f/4, f/8, and so on. This is known as the "f-stop."

A wide aperture creates a shallow depth of field, while a narrow aperture creates a deep depth of field.

HabaneroStrings.infopanel_progressionbody3: <b>All players in a team earn and lose the same amount of progress.</>
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_seasonbody1_c4s4: <b>At the start of every season,</> your ranks in Ranked Modes will reset.
HabaneroStrings.unlockmodal_body2: <b>Complete Ranked Urgent Quests</> to earn unique seasonal rewards.
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_habanerobody1: <b>Eliminate opponents</> and <b>place highly</> to progress through the ranks.
HabaneroStrings.unlockmodal_body1: <b>Play a ranked match</> to reveal your rank. Each mode has its own rank.
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_seasonbody1: <b>Season Zero is the start of ranked play</> and we may need to make adjustments periodically.
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_seasonbody2: At the end of Season Zero <b>your ranked progress will be recorded</> for future reference.
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_seasonbody3_c4s4: At the end of each season, your ranked progress will be recorded for future reference.
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_tournamentbody3: Check the <b>COMPETE</> tab for upcoming tournaments and eligibility requirements.
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_tournamentbody2: Compete to test your skills and earn tournament rewards.
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_rewardsbody2_c5s1: Earn a variety of rewards including Sprays, Emoticons, a Pickaxe, and <b>a Backbling that shows off your rank!</>
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_rewardsbody2_c4s4: Earn a variety of rewards including Sprays, Emoticons, and an <b>Back Bling that shows off your rank!</>
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_rewardsbody2: Earn a variety of rewards including Sprays, Emoticons, and an <b>Emote that shows off your rank!</>
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_progressionbody2: Eliminations later in the match are worth more.
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_rewardsbody1_c5s1: Every match you can progress towards unlocking unique seasonal rewards in ranked by <b>completing Ranked quests.</>
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_rewardsbody1: Every match you'll get a <b>Ranked Urgent Quest.</> Unlock unique seasonal rewards by completing them!
HabaneroStrings.unlockmodal_body3: No new rules to learn. Earn Battle Pass progress as you normally would.
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_unrankedhint: Play 1 match to reveal your rank
HabaneroStrings.infomodal_unrankedmessage:
Play one match to 
reveal your rank
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_unrealbody2: Players who achieve this rank cannot be demoted back to Champion during the season.
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_progressionbody1: Players who dealt damage to an eliminated player earn a share of the progress.
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_leaverpenaltiesbody1:
Players who leave a Ranked Ballistic match early, or disconnect without succeeding to reconnect within a certain time period, will receive a Matchmaking Restriction for Ranked Ballistic, in addition to a Ranked Progression penalty.

Matchmaking Restriction tiers escalate and reset to the prior tier every 12 hours, unless another penalty is incurred.
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_matchmakingbody2: The Team Fill option is only available to solo players in ranked modes.
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_unrealbody1: The highest rank is Unreal. Upon reaching this rank, <b>players are granted a global leaderboard rank</> which is displayed with their badge.
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_tournamentbody1: Unlock access to more tournaments as you rank up.
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_matchmakingbody1:
While in a party, Battle Royale, Fortnite OG and Reload matchmaking is based on the <b>highest-ranked player in the party.</>
In Ballistic, matchmaking is based on the <b>average rank of the party</>
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_protectionbody2: With the First Match Loss Protection, your first match <b>will not reduce your Rank progress</> if you perform poorly.
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_protectionbody1: You will get a First Match Loss Protection, one for Battle Royale and one for Zero Build, that <b>resets daily at 0:00 UTC.</>
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_habanerobody2: You will have a <b>separate rank</> for Battle Royale and Zero Build.
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_seasonbody3: Your final rank in Season Zero will affect your initial rank at the start of the next ranked season.
HabaneroStrings.infopanel_seasonbody2_c4s4: Your final rank in the previous season <b>will affect your initial rank</> at the start of the next season.

ST_EligibilityDescription.Rank: Achieve the required rank in the specified game mode. Check your rank in the Lobby or Career tab.
ST_EligibilityDescription.AgeLock: Be at least 13 years old (or such other age, if greater, as may be required in your country of residence).
ST_EligibilityDescription.MFA: Enable MFA for your account to enhance security. Log into your Epic Games account, open Account, go to the Password & Security section, and enable any of the Two-Factor Methods.
ST_EligibilityDescription.EULA: FortniteÂ® End User License Agreement is a legal document that explains your rights and obligations related to your use of Epicâs Software, including any Services you access or purchases you make through the Software.
ST_EligibilityDescription.SysFlagKernel: HVCI ensures that only trusted code runs in the system's kernel. Enable this feature in your operating systemâs settings under Core Isolation.
ST_EligibilityDescription.SysIOMMU: IOMMU ensures secure device communication and memory isolation. Look it up in your system's BIOS/UEFI settings under options like âIOMMUâ or âVT-dâ (Intel) / âAMD-Viâ (AMD).
ST_EligibilityDescription.AccountLock: Only one account can be used to participate in this event.
ST_EligibilityDescription.RegionLock: Participation is locked to one region.
ST_EligibilityDescription.SysSeqBoot: Secure Boot protects your system by preventing unauthorized software or operating systems from loading during startup. Enable it in your system's BIOS/UEFI settings.
ST_EligibilityDescription.SysCryptoProc: TPM enhances security by providing hardware-based encryption and secure storage. Enable it in your system's BIOS/UEFI settings.
ST_EligibilityDescription.SysNotVM: Tournament participation is only allowed on physical devices. Virtual machines or emulated environments are not supported. Ensure that you are playing directly on a physical machine to meet this requirement.
ST_EligibilityDescription.TeamLock: You can only queue with one team in this event.
ST_EligibilityDescription.QualifyingRound: You must complete all required qualifying rounds to be eligible for the event. Check your progress in the tournament tab.
ST_EligibilityDescription.SeasonNumberOfPlayerMatches: You must meet the participation requirements by taking part in a minimum number of events.
ST_EligibilityDescription.TotalNumOfPlayerMatches: You must meet the participation requirements by taking part in a minimum number of events.
ST_EligibilityDescription.NoTokens: Your account is ineligible for this event.
ST_EligibilityDescription.SuspiciousBehaviour: Your account is ineligible for this event.
ST_EligibilityDescription.AccountLevel: Your account should meet the minimum level requirement. Check your progress in the Profile section.
ST_EligibilityDescription.SysOSVersion: Your operating system must be a stable release of Windows. Beta or preview versions are not supported. Ensure you are using a fully updated and supported version.
ST_EligibilityDescription.SysInjection: Your system must block unauthorized injection of code or processes into running applications. This feature is generally enabled by default but can be configured in your security or antivirus software.
